The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Puducherry, Nov. 28 (PTI): A 21-year-old girl refused to marry a man who demanded more dowry a few minutes before the wedding on Friday.           
	The groom had already been given 15 gold sovereigns. The girl married a relative present at the wedding with the consent of her parents.                  
	 Durban (PTI): An Indian-origin schoolteacher survived after being thrown off a 60-metre-high-bridge by thugs. Kavisha Seevnarain, 26, who was left with a broken rib, had been waylaid at gunpoint by three thugs who made her drive around before throwing her off the bridge into a river. Seevnarain was saved by a passer-by.                  
	 Mainpuri (PTI): The Mainpuri district administration has suspended 41 teachers who were found absent during surprise checks on primary schools. It has also ordered deduction of a days salary.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): Security forces shot dead a Hizb-ul Mujahideen militant during an encounter in Kishtwar district on Friday.                                                                                                                                              
